1260
01:20:32,619 --> 01:20:34,121
<i>And they have a child.</i>

1261
01:20:34,246 --> 01:20:38,797
<i>So Rodriguez has a South African
grandson, a South African grandchild.</i>

1262
01:20:38,917 --> 01:20:42,296
<i>For me, I used to be a jeweler
in Johannesburg.</i>

1263
01:20:42,296 --> 01:20:44,765
<i>I now live in Cape Town
and have a music store.</i>

1264
01:20:44,757 --> 01:20:47,761
<i>Things changed so much for us.</i>

1265
01:20:47,885 --> 01:20:50,263
<i>But, except for one person,
and that's Rodriguez.</i>

1266
01:20:50,262 --> 01:20:52,481
<i>For him, nothing has changed.</i>

1267
01:20:52,473 --> 01:20:56,103
<i>The life that he was living
is still the life that he's living now.</i>

1268
01:20:56,101 --> 01:21:00,322
<i>(Emmerson) What he's demonstrated
very clearly is that you have a choice.</i>

1269
01:21:00,314 --> 01:21:03,488
<i>He took all that torment,
all that agony,</i>

1270
01:21:03,484 --> 01:21:05,612
<i>all that confusion and pain,</i>

1271
01:21:05,611 --> 01:21:08,410
<i>and he transformed it
into something beautiful.</i>

1272
01:21:09,114 --> 01:21:11,387
He's like the silk worm, you know?

1273
01:21:11,483 --> 01:21:16,460
You take this raw material
and you transform it.

1274
01:21:16,580 --> 01:21:19,959
And you come out with something
that wasn't there before.

1275
01:21:20,084 --> 01:21:21,506
Something beautiful.

1276
01:21:21,502 --> 01:21:25,348
Something perhaps transcendent.
Something perhaps eternal.

1277
01:21:25,464 --> 01:21:27,512
<i>Insofar as he does that,</i>

1278
01:21:27,633 --> 01:21:32,810
<i>I think he's representative
of the human spirit, of what's possible.</i>

1279
01:21:32,805 --> 01:21:36,480
<i>That you have a choice.
"And this has been my choice,</i>

1280
01:21:36,475 --> 01:21:38,694
"to give you <i>Sugar Man</i>".

1281
01:21:38,685 --> 01:21:40,813
<i>Now, have you done that? Ask yourself.</i>

